CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 10, 1953, pg. 21, reads: "Closing The Deal - The closing ceremonies took place at the local offices of the Federal Housing Administration last week. Among those present were, seated, Mrs. R.L. Vann and Jesse McFarland, local FHA administrator.  Standing: Charles Levitt, Russell L. Hauser, assistant vice president, Chemical Bank and Trust Company, mortgagor; Mrs. Helen Prattis, secretary, Belmar Gardens, Inc.; William Brafman, sponsor; Clarence Rodgers, office manager; Nicholas LeDonne and J. Burton Norris, counsel for the FHA."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, seated from left: Jessie Vann and Jesse McFarland; standing: Charles Levitt, Russell L. Hauser, Helen Prattis, William Brafman, Clarence Rodgers, Nicholas LeDonne, and J. Burton Norris, gathered in Federal Housing Administration office for closing of Belmar Gardens, another version
